246// This is a cut-down version of what CMake's `GenerateExportHeader` would usually generate. To
247// simplify builds without CMake, we define these things manually instead of relying on CMake
248// to generate the header.
249//
250// For static builds, our CMakeList will define `ZYCORE_STATIC_BUILD`. For shared library builds,
251// our CMake will define `ZYCORE_SHOULD_EXPORT` depending on whether the target is being imported or
252// exported. If CMake isn't used, users can manually define these to fit their use-case.
253
254// Backward compatibility: CMake would previously generate these variables names. However, because
255// they have pretty cryptic names, we renamed them when we got rid of `GenerateExportHeader`. For
256// backward compatibility for users that don't use CMake and previously manually defined these, we
257// translate the old defines here and print a warning.
258#if defined(ZYCORE_STATIC_DEFINE)
259# pragma message("ZYCORE_STATIC_DEFINE was renamed to ZYCORE_STATIC_BUILD.")
260# define ZYCORE_STATIC_BUILD
261#endif
262#if defined(Zycore_EXPORTS)
263# pragma message("Zycore_EXPORTS was renamed to ZYCORE_SHOULD_EXPORT.")
264# define ZYCORE_SHOULD_EXPORT
265#endif
266
270#if defined(ZYCORE_STATIC_BUILD)
271# define ZYCORE_EXPORT
272#else
273# if defined(ZYCORE_SHOULD_EXPORT)
274# define ZYCORE_EXPORT ZYAN_DLLEXPORT
275# else
276# define ZYCORE_EXPORT ZYAN_DLLIMPORT
277# endif
278#endif
279
283#define ZYCORE_NO_EXPORT

530/*
531 * Checks, if the bit at index `b` is required to present the ordinal value `n`.
532 *
533 * @param n The ordinal value.
534 * @param b The bit index.
535 *
536 * @return `ZYAN_TRUE`, if the bit at index `b` is required to present the ordinal value `n` or
537 * `ZYAN_FALSE`, if not.
538 *
539 * Note that this macro always returns `ZYAN_FALSE` for `n == 0`.
540 */
541#define ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, b) (((unsigned long)(n) >> (b)) > 0)
542
543/*
544 * Returns the number of bits required to represent the ordinal value `n`.
545 *
546 * @param n The ordinal value.
547 *
548 * @return The number of bits required to represent the ordinal value `n`.
549 *
550 * Note that this macro returns `0` for `n == 0`.
551 */
552#define ZYAN_BITS_TO_REPRESENT(n) \
553 ( \
554 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 0) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 1) + \
555 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 2) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 3) + \
556 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 4) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 5) + \
557 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 6) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 7) + \
558 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 8) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 9) + \
559 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 10) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 11) + \
560 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 12) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 13) + \
561 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 14) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 15) + \
562 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 16) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 17) + \
563 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 18) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 19) + \
564 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 20) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 21) + \
565 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 22) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 23) + \
566 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 24) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 25) + \
567 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 26) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 27) + \
568 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 28) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 29) + \
569 ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 30) + ZYAN_NEEDS_BIT(n, 31) \
570 )
571

624#if defined(ZYAN_NO_LIBC) || \
625 (defined(ZYAN_MSVC) && defined(ZYAN_KERNEL)) // The WDK LibC lacks stdint.h.
626 // No LibC mode, use compiler built-in types / macros.
627# if defined(ZYAN_MSVC) || defined(ZYAN_ICC)
628 typedef unsigned __int8 ZyanU8;
629 typedef unsigned __int16 ZyanU16;
630 typedef unsigned __int32 ZyanU32;
631 typedef unsigned __int64 ZyanU64;
632 typedef signed __int8 ZyanI8;
633 typedef signed __int16 ZyanI16;
634 typedef signed __int32 ZyanI32;
635 typedef signed __int64 ZyanI64;
636# if _WIN64
637 typedef ZyanU64 ZyanUSize;
638 typedef ZyanI64 ZyanISize;
639 typedef ZyanU64 ZyanUPointer;
640 typedef ZyanI64 ZyanIPointer;
641# else
642 typedef ZyanU32 ZyanUSize;
643 typedef ZyanI32 ZyanISize;
644 typedef ZyanU32 ZyanUPointer;
645 typedef ZyanI32 ZyanIPointer;
646# endif
647# elif defined(ZYAN_GNUC)
648 typedef __UINT8_TYPE__ ZyanU8;
649 typedef __UINT16_TYPE__ ZyanU16;
650 typedef __UINT32_TYPE__ ZyanU32;
651 typedef __UINT64_TYPE__ ZyanU64;
652 typedef __INT8_TYPE__ ZyanI8;
653 typedef __INT16_TYPE__ ZyanI16;
654 typedef __INT32_TYPE__ ZyanI32;
655 typedef __INT64_TYPE__ ZyanI64;
656 typedef __SIZE_TYPE__ ZyanUSize;
657 typedef __PTRDIFF_TYPE__ ZyanISize;
658 typedef __UINTPTR_TYPE__ ZyanUPointer;
659 typedef __INTPTR_TYPE__ ZyanIPointer;
660# else
661# error "Unsupported compiler for no-libc mode."
662# endif
663
664# if defined(ZYAN_MSVC)
665# define ZYAN_INT8_MIN (-127i8 - 1)
666# define ZYAN_INT16_MIN (-32767i16 - 1)
667# define ZYAN_INT32_MIN (-2147483647i32 - 1)
668# define ZYAN_INT64_MIN (-9223372036854775807i64 - 1)
669# define ZYAN_INT8_MAX 127i8
670# define ZYAN_INT16_MAX 32767i16
671# define ZYAN_INT32_MAX 2147483647i32
672# define ZYAN_INT64_MAX 9223372036854775807i64
673# define ZYAN_UINT8_MAX 0xffui8
674# define ZYAN_UINT16_MAX 0xffffui16
675# define ZYAN_UINT32_MAX 0xffffffffui32
676# define ZYAN_UINT64_MAX 0xffffffffffffffffui64
677# else
678# define ZYAN_INT8_MAX __INT8_MAX__
679# define ZYAN_INT8_MIN (-ZYAN_INT8_MAX - 1)
680# define ZYAN_INT16_MAX __INT16_MAX__
681# define ZYAN_INT16_MIN (-ZYAN_INT16_MAX - 1)
682# define ZYAN_INT32_MAX __INT32_MAX__
683# define ZYAN_INT32_MIN (-ZYAN_INT32_MAX - 1)
684# define ZYAN_INT64_MAX __INT64_MAX__
685# define ZYAN_INT64_MIN (-ZYAN_INT64_MAX - 1)
686# define ZYAN_UINT8_MAX __UINT8_MAX__
687# define ZYAN_UINT16_MAX __UINT16_MAX__
688# define ZYAN_UINT32_MAX __UINT32_MAX__
689# define ZYAN_UINT64_MAX __UINT64_MAX__
690# endif
691#else
692 // If is LibC present, we use stdint types.
693# include <stdint.h>
694# include <stddef.h>
695 typedef uint8_t ZyanU8;
696 typedef uint16_t ZyanU16;
697 typedef uint32_t ZyanU32;
698 typedef uint64_t ZyanU64;
699 typedef int8_t ZyanI8;
700 typedef int16_t ZyanI16;
701 typedef int32_t ZyanI32;
702 typedef int64_t ZyanI64;
703 typedef size_t ZyanUSize;
704 typedef ptrdiff_t ZyanISize;
705 typedef uintptr_t ZyanUPointer;
706 typedef intptr_t ZyanIPointer;
707
708# define ZYAN_INT8_MIN INT8_MIN
709# define ZYAN_INT16_MIN INT16_MIN
710# define ZYAN_INT32_MIN INT32_MIN
711# define ZYAN_INT64_MIN INT64_MIN
712# define ZYAN_INT8_MAX INT8_MAX
713# define ZYAN_INT16_MAX INT16_MAX
714# define ZYAN_INT32_MAX INT32_MAX
715# define ZYAN_INT64_MAX INT64_MAX
716# define ZYAN_UINT8_MAX UINT8_MAX
717# define ZYAN_UINT16_MAX UINT16_MAX
718# define ZYAN_UINT32_MAX UINT32_MAX
719# define ZYAN_UINT64_MAX UINT64_MAX
720#endif

722// Verify size assumptions.
723ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanU8 ) == 1 );
724ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanU16 ) == 2 );
725ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanU32 ) == 4 );
726ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanU64 ) == 8 );
727ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanI8 ) == 1 );
728ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanI16 ) == 2 );
729ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanI32 ) == 4 );
730ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanI64 ) == 8 );
731ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanUSize ) == sizeof(void*)); // TODO: This one is incorrect!
732ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanISize ) == sizeof(void*)); // TODO: This one is incorrect!
733ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanUPointer) == sizeof(void*));
734ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(ZyanIPointer) == sizeof(void*));
735
736// Verify signedness assumptions (relies on size checks above).
737ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT((ZyanI8 )-1 >> 1 < (ZyanI8 )((ZyanU8 )-1 >> 1));
738ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT((ZyanI16)-1 >> 1 < (ZyanI16)((ZyanU16)-1 >> 1));
739ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT((ZyanI32)-1 >> 1 < (ZyanI32)((ZyanU32)-1 >> 1));
740ZYAN_STATIC_ASSERT((ZyanI64)-1 >> 1 < (ZyanI64)((ZyanU64)-1 >> 1));

993#ifndef ZYDIS_DEFINES_H
994#define ZYDIS_DEFINES_H

996
997// This is a cut-down version of what CMake's `GenerateExportHeader` would usually generate. To
998// simplify builds without CMake, we define these things manually instead of relying on CMake
999// to generate the header.
1000//
1001// For static builds, our CMakeList will define `ZYDIS_STATIC_BUILD`. For shared library builds,
1002// our CMake will define `ZYDIS_SHOULD_EXPORT` depending on whether the target is being imported or
1003// exported. If CMake isn't used, users can manually define these to fit their use-case.
1004
1005// Backward compatibility: CMake would previously generate these variables names. However, because
1006// they have pretty cryptic names, we renamed them when we got rid of `GenerateExportHeader`. For
1007// backward compatibility for users that don't use CMake and previously manually defined these, we
1008// translate the old defines here and print a warning.
1009#if defined(ZYDIS_STATIC_DEFINE)
1010# pragma message("ZYDIS_STATIC_DEFINE was renamed to ZYDIS_STATIC_BUILD.")
1011# define ZYDIS_STATIC_BUILD
1012#endif
1013#if defined(Zydis_EXPORTS)
1014# pragma message("Zydis_EXPORTS was renamed to ZYDIS_SHOULD_EXPORT.")
1015# define ZYDIS_SHOULD_EXPORT
1016#endif
1017
1021#if defined(ZYDIS_STATIC_BUILD)
1022# define ZYDIS_EXPORT
1023#else
1024# if defined(ZYDIS_SHOULD_EXPORT)
1025# define ZYDIS_EXPORT ZYAN_DLLEXPORT
1026# else
1027# define ZYDIS_EXPORT ZYAN_DLLIMPORT
1028# endif
1029#endif
1030
1034#define ZYDIS_NO_EXPORT
1035
1036#endif // ZYDIS_DEFINES_H
1037

1039extern "C" {
1040#endif

6445/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

6447/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

6458#define ZYAN_MAKE_STATUS(error, module, code) \
6459 (ZyanStatus)((((error) & 0x01u) << 31u) | (((module) & 0x7FFu) << 20u) | ((code) & 0xFFFFFu))
6460
6461/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
6462/* Checks */
6463/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
6464
6472#define ZYAN_SUCCESS(status) \
6473 (!((status) & 0x80000000u))
6474
6482#define ZYAN_FAILED(status) \
6483 ((status) & 0x80000000u)
6484
6490#define ZYAN_CHECK(status) \
6491 do \
6492 { \
6493 const ZyanStatus status_047620348 = (status); \
6494 if (!ZYAN_SUCCESS(status_047620348)) \
6495 { \
6496 return status_047620348; \
6497 } \
6498 } while (0)
6499
6500/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
6501/* Information */
6502/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
6503
6511#define ZYAN_STATUS_MODULE(status) \
6512 (((status) >> 20) & 0x7FFu)
6513
6521#define ZYAN_STATUS_CODE(status) \
6522 ((status) & 0xFFFFFu)

7865#ifndef ZYCORE_COMPARISON_H
7866#define ZYCORE_COMPARISON_H
7867
7868
7869#ifdef __cplusplus
7870extern "C" {
7871#endif
7872
7873/* ============================================================================================== */
7874/* Enums and types */
7875/* ============================================================================================== */
7876
7886typedef ZyanBool (*ZyanEqualityComparison)(const void* left, const void* right);
7887
7899typedef ZyanI32 (*ZyanComparison)(const void* left, const void* right);
7900
7901/* ============================================================================================== */
7902/* Macros */
7903/* ============================================================================================== */
7904
7905/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
7906/* Equality comparison functions */
7907/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
7908
7915#define ZYAN_DECLARE_EQUALITY_COMPARISON(name, type) \
7916 ZyanBool name(const type* left, const type* right) \
7917 { \
7918 ZYAN_ASSERT(left); \
7919 ZYAN_ASSERT(right); \
7920 \
7921 return (*left == *right) ? ZYAN_TRUE : ZYAN_FALSE; \
7922 }
7923
7932#define ZYAN_DECLARE_EQUALITY_COMPARISON_FOR_FIELD(name, type, field_name) \
7933 ZyanBool name(const type* left, const type* right) \
7934 { \
7935 ZYAN_ASSERT(left); \
7936 ZYAN_ASSERT(right); \
7937 \
7938 return (left->field_name == right->field_name) ? ZYAN_TRUE : ZYAN_FALSE; \
7939 }
7940
7941/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
7942/* Comparison functions */
7943/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
7944
7951#define ZYAN_DECLARE_COMPARISON(name, type) \
7952 ZyanI32 name(const type* left, const type* right) \
7953 { \
7954 ZYAN_ASSERT(left); \
7955 ZYAN_ASSERT(right); \
7956 \
7957 if (*left < *right) \
7958 { \
7959 return -1; \
7960 } \
7961 if (*left > *right) \
7962 { \
7963 return 1; \
7964 } \
7965 return 0; \
7966 }
7967
7976#define ZYAN_DECLARE_COMPARISON_FOR_FIELD(name, type, field_name) \
7977 ZyanI32 name(const type* left, const type* right) \
7978 { \
7979 ZYAN_ASSERT(left); \
7980 ZYAN_ASSERT(right); \
7981 \
7982 if (left->field_name < right->field_name) \
7983 { \
7984 return -1; \
7985 } \
7986 if (left->field_name > right->field_name) \
7987 { \
7988 return 1; \
7989 } \
7990 return 0; \
7991 }
7992
7993 /* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
7994
7995/* ============================================================================================== */
7996/* Exported functions */
7997/* ============================================================================================== */
7998
7999/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
8000/* Default equality comparison functions */
8001/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
8002
8012ZYAN_INLINE ZYAN_DECLARE_EQUALITY_COMPARISON(ZyanEqualsPointer, void* const)
8013
8014
8023ZYAN_INLINE ZYAN_DECLARE_EQUALITY_COMPARISON(ZyanEqualsBool, ZyanBool)
8024

8289 ZyanU8 shrink_threshold;

8301 ZyanUSize element_size;
8305 ZyanMemberProcedure destructor;

8324 { \
8325 /* allocator */ ZYAN_NULL, \
8326 /* growth_factor */ 0, \
8327 /* shrink_threshold */ 0, \
8328 /* size */ 0, \
8329 /* capacity */ 0, \
8330 /* element_size */ 0, \
8331 /* destructor */ ZYAN_NULL, \
8332 /* data */ ZYAN_NULL \
8333 }
8334
8335/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
8336/* Helper macros */
8337/* ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
8338
8350#ifdef __cplusplus
8351#define ZYAN_VECTOR_GET(type, vector, index) \
8352 (*reinterpret_cast<const type*>(ZyanVectorGet(vector, index)))
8353#else
8354#define ZYAN_VECTOR_GET(type, vector, index) \
8355 (*(const type*)ZyanVectorGet(vector, index))
8356#endif
8357
8366#define ZYAN_VECTOR_FOREACH(type, vector, item_name, body) \
8367 { \
8368 const ZyanUSize ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(size_d50d3303, item_name) = (vector)->size; \
8369 for (ZyanUSize ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(i_bfd62679, item_name) = 0; \
8370 ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(i_bfd62679, item_name) < \
8371 ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(size_d50d3303, item_name); \
8372 ++ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(i_bfd62679, item_name)) \
8373 { \
8374 const type item_name = ZYAN_VECTOR_GET(type, vector, \
8375 ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(i_bfd62679, item_name)); \
8376 body \
8377 } \
8378 }
8379
8388#define ZYAN_VECTOR_FOREACH_MUTABLE(type, vector, item_name, body) \
8389 { \
8390 const ZyanUSize ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(size_d50d3303, item_name) = (vector)->size; \
8391 for (ZyanUSize ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(i_bfd62679, item_name) = 0; \
8392 ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(i_bfd62679, item_name) < \
8393 ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(size_d50d3303, item_name); \
8394 ++ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(i_bfd62679, item_name)) \
8395 { \
8396 type* const item_name = ZyanVectorGetMutable(vector, \
8397 ZYAN_MACRO_CONCAT_EXPAND(i_bfd62679, item_name)); \
8398 body \
8399 } \
8400 }
